Get a random vector of species names.

Source: R/names_list.r
names_list.Rd

Family and order names come from the APG plant names list. Genus and species names come from Theplantlist.org.

names_list(rank = "genus", size = 10)

Arguments

rank

(character) Taxonomic rank, one of species, genus (default), family, order

size

(integer/numeric) Number of names to get. Maximum depends on the rank

Value

character vector of taxonomic names

Author

Scott Chamberlain

Examples

names_list()
#>  [1] "Stachytarpheta" "Lachenalia"     "Catachaetum"    "Notothylas"    
#>  [5] "Kickxia"        "Hydnophytum"    "Suberanthus"    "Chresta"       
#>  [9] "Cissus"         "Aristida"      
names_list('species')
#>  [1] "Scutellaria titovii"       "Artanthe mikaniana"       
#>  [3] "Heterolepis oryzoides"     "Metzgeria atramentaria"   
#>  [5] "Alicularia pachyphylla"    "Tragacantha segethii"     
#>  [7] "Thereianthus bracteolatus" "Scottellia kamerunensis"  
#>  [9] "Solenostoma patoniae"      "Pterocarpus mexicanus"    
names_list('genus')
#>  [1] "Actinocephalus" "Zamia"          "Macaranga"      "Perovskia"     
#>  [5] "Scaphyglottis"  "Grewia"         "Sarcosperma"    "Amphidasya"    
#>  [9] "Upopion"        "Rhaphidophora" 
names_list('family')
#>  [1] "Lamiaceae"        "Meliaceae"        "Asparagaceae"     "Asteraceae"      
#>  [5] "Solanaceae"       "Platanaceae"      "Dioscoreaceae"    "Apiaceae"        
#>  [9] "Hydrostachyaceae" "Loganiaceae"     
names_list('order')
#>  [1] "Caryophyllales" "Saxifragales"   "Bruniales"      "Poales"        
#>  [5] "Alismatales"    "Rosales"        "Myrtales"       "Asterales"     
#>  [9] "Lamiales"       "Salviniales"   
names_list('order', 2)
#> [1] "Pandanales" "Sapindales"
names_list('order', 15)
#>  [1] "Ericales"     "Asterales"    "Dioscoreales" "Cycadales"    "Liliales"    
#>  [6] "Rosales"      "Lamiales"     "Pandanales"   "Lamiales"     "Brassicales" 
#> [11] "Malvales"     "Myrtales"     "Alismatales"  "Asterales"    "Celastrales" 

# You can get a lot of genus or species names if you want
nrow(theplantlist)
#> [1] 10000
